{
  "texts": [
    "Over the past decade, ML has been increasingly applied to BPS, fueled in part by the emergence of the IoT and the need for computationally tractable predictions.",
    "ML has been used during the design stage to augment generative design and parametric simulations.",
    "Deep generative algorithms such as Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) (Huang and Zheng, 2018; Nauata et al., 2020) have been proposed for generating diverse but realistic architectural floorplans that are known to be a time-consuming iterative process.",
    "The automated generation of architectural floorplans can be coupled with BPS tools to systematically explore architectural layouts that optimize building energy efficiency (Gan et al., 2019).",
    "Metamodeling, defined as the practice of using a model to describe another model as an instance (Allemang et al., 2011), is another aspect where ML has been extensively applied to BPS throughout the building lifecycle."
  ]
}